WEBVTT

00:42.477 --> 00:45.175
-  Amen.
-  Amen.

01:10.200 --> 01:12.942
- Amen.
-  Amen.

01:20.645 --> 01:23.822
- Amen.
- Amen.

02:11.609 --> 02:13.437
I could always
visit you in Edinburgh.

02:13.568 --> 02:17.093
But I love our sexy
<i>Notting Hill</i> weekends.
Don't you?

02:17.224 --> 02:20.401
Of course.
I love the movie.

02:20.531 --> 02:22.620
I love that you
love the movie.

02:22.751 --> 02:25.319
- I love our time together.
- You silly thing.

02:26.885 --> 02:28.452
You'll miss your plane.

02:30.846 --> 02:32.369
My friends say you've got
another woman back home

02:32.500 --> 02:33.805
and three kids named Jock.

02:34.850 --> 02:36.678
That is not true!

02:36.808 --> 02:38.549
It's five kids,

02:38.680 --> 02:41.813
and only two of them
are named Jock.

02:42.858 --> 02:44.860
Who cares what your friends
say, anyway?

02:44.990 --> 02:47.602
Well, I do. They're
the closest thing I have
to family--

02:47.732 --> 02:50.387
I get it, I get it.
I met them, remember?

02:50.518 --> 02:52.172
Ah, yes.

02:52.302 --> 02:54.870
I... I admit they were
a little off the charts

02:55.000 --> 02:57.481
and possibly
off their meds.

02:59.396 --> 03:01.093
Are you sure you want us
to move in together?

03:01.224 --> 03:03.444
Of course I do. I...

03:03.574 --> 03:06.621
I just need a few months
to get things sorted out.

03:06.751 --> 03:08.536
A few months?

03:08.666 --> 03:10.625
You know, it only took them
six weeks to film
<i>Notting Hill.</i>

03:10.755 --> 03:12.627
- It's not that long.

03:12.757 --> 03:15.543
I know. I just...
I hate goodbyes

03:15.673 --> 03:17.458
and it just seems
like my life

03:17.588 --> 03:19.634
is permanently on hold
with customer services.

03:22.767 --> 03:25.553
We'll fix that
as soon as I return,
my darling.

03:27.990 --> 03:29.165
I'll come see you off.

03:29.296 --> 03:31.994
No, no, no, no.
You stay where you are.

03:32.124 --> 03:33.604
You know I hate goodbyes.

03:36.738 --> 03:38.392
I love you.

03:43.310 --> 03:44.441
Claire Chambers.

03:45.312 --> 03:46.487
I love you.

03:51.883 --> 03:52.841
Is that your phone?

03:53.624 --> 03:55.670
Oh, no.

03:55.800 --> 03:57.019
Richard!

04:09.031 --> 04:10.119
- Ugh.

04:21.783 --> 04:22.827
Eww!

04:23.828 --> 04:25.090
Agh!

04:39.627 --> 04:41.150
Claire, I'm in the middle
of a lesson.

04:41.281 --> 04:42.934
It's happened again.

04:43.065 --> 04:44.327
What?

04:44.458 --> 04:47.896
I need wisdom,
and wine, and chocolate.

04:48.897 --> 04:52.204
And tell Theo.
I need Theo.

05:00.996 --> 05:02.476
Hello, gorgeous.

05:02.606 --> 05:03.738
It's Claire.

05:03.868 --> 05:06.915
What's the guy
done this time?

05:07.045 --> 05:08.699
We're on the break-up
duty again.

05:08.830 --> 05:10.179
Been summoned
to the depression den.

05:10.310 --> 05:12.616
Oh, it'll be
that ghastly Scotsman

05:12.747 --> 05:15.184
with his funny combover
and Windsor knots.

05:15.315 --> 05:17.708
I knew this would happen.
I never trusted him.

05:17.839 --> 05:19.406
He's got snake eyes.
I said to her,

05:19.536 --> 05:20.581
"He's got snake eyes."

05:20.711 --> 05:22.060
Theo!

05:22.191 --> 05:23.366
Oh, calm down, bitch!
I'm already on my way.

05:23.497 --> 05:25.542
And I know,
bring chocolate.

05:28.763 --> 05:31.592
- Um, how do you
not remember Richard?
- I...

05:32.593 --> 05:35.378
Clara, in my defense,

05:35.509 --> 05:36.988
there've been very, very, very

05:37.119 --> 05:38.903
- many, many, many, many,
many men.
- Mm-hmm.

05:39.034 --> 05:43.212
Not that many.
Just like five.

05:43.343 --> 05:45.040
- This year.
- Okay, whatever.

05:45.170 --> 05:47.172
I'm nearly 40.
I'm bound to have a history.

05:47.303 --> 05:48.783
- Is that him?

05:48.913 --> 05:49.958
Is that the pig?

05:50.088 --> 05:52.308
Oh, it'll be
my friend Caroline.

05:52.439 --> 05:55.093
Her wedding venue burned down.
She's hysterical.

05:56.356 --> 05:58.270
At least she has a fiancé.

05:58.401 --> 06:01.230
Well, this is clearly
all my fault.
What did I do wrong?

06:01.361 --> 06:02.840
Oh, darling,
be like me.

06:02.971 --> 06:04.407
Take a vow of celibacy.

06:04.538 --> 06:05.669
Now...

06:05.800 --> 06:07.062
Ooh.

06:09.673 --> 06:10.587
There.

06:11.980 --> 06:13.285
Thanks.

06:14.461 --> 06:15.679
Oh, my God.

06:15.810 --> 06:16.985
If that is your friend
with her wedding--

06:17.115 --> 06:19.770
- Oh, it's Ben.
- Oooh! Ben!

06:19.901 --> 06:22.033
<i>Claire!
How are you, darling?</i>

06:22.164 --> 06:25.080
-  Hey, Ben!
<i>- You're all there.</i>

06:25.210 --> 06:27.212
We're all here.
We're on a, you know,
mercy mission.

06:27.343 --> 06:28.562
<i>Hey, guys.</i>

06:28.692 --> 06:30.259
I'm sorry to interrupt,
but I'm calling you

06:30.390 --> 06:32.914
'cause I got a little news
that I need to share with you.

06:33.044 --> 06:34.655
Arnie Sandoval died.

06:34.785 --> 06:38.049
Oh, my God!
Arnie Sandoval died?!

06:38.180 --> 06:41.183
Arnie... hmm.
Who is Arnie Sandoval?

06:41.313 --> 06:45.579
Apparently, he's
my biological father.

06:45.709 --> 06:47.581
- What?!
- What?!

06:47.711 --> 06:50.061
Ben, you don't have
a father.

06:50.192 --> 06:52.237
I mean-- I mean,
who was he?

06:52.368 --> 06:55.937
He's from Saint Kitts and Nevis.
It's a-- it's a--

06:56.067 --> 06:58.766
<i>an island in the Caribbean,
the West Indies.</i>

06:58.896 --> 07:00.550
And apparently,
I'm his only heir

07:00.681 --> 07:02.900
and I inherited his estate.

07:03.031 --> 07:05.033
Wait, I'm sorry.

07:05.163 --> 07:07.644
Ben, how do you feel
about all this?

07:07.775 --> 07:10.473
I'm just trying to wrap my head
around this whole thing.

07:10.604 --> 07:12.736
I'm-- I'm a bit confused.

07:12.867 --> 07:15.783
<i>And I need you guys.
I really do. I...</i>

07:15.913 --> 07:17.437
I want you to come with me

07:17.567 --> 07:20.396
because I need to go down there
and sign some papers and--

07:20.527 --> 07:23.704
and, um, I don't think
I can do this thing alone.

07:23.834 --> 07:26.054
<i>So, my dear friends,</i>

07:26.184 --> 07:29.274
I'm asking you to go
on a little adventure with me.

07:29.405 --> 07:32.495
Oh, yes.
Yes, yes, yes.

07:32.626 --> 07:36.456
<i>I'll see you next week, guys.
I love you all. Thank you.</i>

07:36.586 --> 07:37.892
- Oh...
- Bye.

07:43.071 --> 07:45.595
- Oh, my God! What?!

07:55.257 --> 07:56.824
Ben Katzman.

07:59.914 --> 08:01.306
You lucky bastard.

08:01.437 --> 08:04.571
Baby, what's up?

08:04.701 --> 08:06.398
Nothing, darling.
Go back to sleep.

08:06.529 --> 08:09.097
Mm. Who called so early?

08:09.227 --> 08:10.359
It was Ben.

08:11.839 --> 08:13.971
He just inherited
some property
in the Caribbean.

08:14.102 --> 08:16.191
Mm-hmm.

08:16.321 --> 08:19.629
He wants to know
if we'd like to go
for a week's vacation there.

08:19.760 --> 08:23.024
Well, who wouldn't?

08:23.154 --> 08:24.982
He's paying for everything.

08:25.113 --> 08:27.898
What? What?
Are you serious?

08:28.029 --> 08:29.596
- Oh, my God.
- Seriously.

08:29.726 --> 08:32.947
- Seriously.

08:33.077 --> 08:34.688
He's inviting Alex.

08:35.863 --> 08:36.820
Are you okay with that?

08:36.951 --> 08:38.387
Of course
I'm okay with that.

08:38.518 --> 08:41.782
Why wouldn't I be?
You married me.

08:45.612 --> 08:47.614
- Does that mean--
- Yes!

08:47.744 --> 08:49.180
Yes, baby. We're going.

09:02.803 --> 09:05.022
Baby, you look amazing.

09:06.807 --> 09:08.809
She's gotta stop
taking selfies.

09:10.375 --> 09:12.421
There they are!
Well, hey!

09:12.552 --> 09:14.075
Claire! Theo!

09:18.514 --> 09:20.298
Oh, my God!

09:30.874 --> 09:33.050
-  Oh, my God!
- Thank you so much
for being here.

09:33.181 --> 09:35.749
You look so beautiful.
Thank you all,
you all look beautiful.

09:35.879 --> 09:37.620
I have an announcement
to make.

09:37.751 --> 09:40.057
Claire is no longer
in the market for love,

09:40.188 --> 09:41.319
and Alex is just here
for sex.

09:41.450 --> 09:42.538
- Oh.
- Mm-hmm.

09:42.669 --> 09:44.105
And by the way,
the driver looks good.

09:44.235 --> 09:47.543
Hello, sir!
Hello!

09:47.674 --> 09:49.197
Oh, Theo, you old queen!
Come here.

09:49.327 --> 09:51.416
Oh, oh. Stop it,
stop it, stop it.

09:51.547 --> 09:52.896
Don't stop it!
Don't stop it!

09:53.027 --> 09:55.986
Megan, your husband
just assaulted me.

09:56.117 --> 09:58.380
Oh, no. I'm sure
he was just kidding.

09:58.510 --> 09:59.903
Ba-baby, tell him
you're just kidding.

10:00.034 --> 10:02.079
Baby, it's a joke.

10:02.210 --> 10:03.864
Come on, guys! Let's get
on the boat. Here we go.

10:03.994 --> 10:05.343
- Yes!
- Let's go!

10:05.474 --> 10:06.388
Oh, my God!

10:40.944 --> 10:43.077
<i>Welcome to Nevis.
Charlie Brooks,
your father's lawyer.</i>

10:43.207 --> 10:44.513
We spoke on the phone.

10:44.644 --> 10:46.515
Yes. It's a pleasure
to meet you, sir.

10:46.646 --> 10:48.169
Hello, Charlie.

11:28.339 --> 11:31.342
Oh, Ben.
It's beautiful.

11:38.219 --> 11:40.134
I love it.

11:40.264 --> 11:44.225
Oh, my God.
It's so beautiful, babe.

11:44.355 --> 11:46.357
All the pretty trees!

11:55.366 --> 11:56.890
Ben Katzman.

11:57.020 --> 11:59.022
You're a lucky bastard.

11:59.153 --> 12:01.242
If I were you,
I'd stay here forever.

12:01.372 --> 12:03.244
Look who's here.
They're here.

12:03.374 --> 12:04.636
-  Hello.
- Hi.

12:04.767 --> 12:06.029
- Welcome, Mr. Katzman.
- Hi. Hi.

12:06.160 --> 12:08.075
I'm Sheldon,
your father's butler,

12:08.205 --> 12:10.033
and this is
my wife, Lois.

12:10.164 --> 12:12.079
- Hello. It's such a pleasure
to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

12:12.209 --> 12:13.776
- This place is--
- Magical.

12:13.907 --> 12:15.560
Magical. Yes, it is.

12:15.691 --> 12:18.476
Mr. Katzman, my wife and I
are deeply sorry
for your loss.

12:18.607 --> 12:20.740
I'm so, so sorry to interrupt,

12:20.870 --> 12:22.829
but I really have
to use the bathroom.

12:22.959 --> 12:24.482
- I'll take you.
- Okay. Thank you.

12:24.613 --> 12:26.354
And please, I'm sorry,
but I'm dying for a shower.

12:26.484 --> 12:27.703
It's way too hot for me.

12:27.834 --> 12:29.705
Yeah, I'll take you
to your room.

12:29.836 --> 12:31.751
- Are you Claire?
- Yes. I am.

12:31.881 --> 12:33.535
Nice to meet you.
And are you Theo?

12:33.665 --> 12:34.797
- I am.
- Yes.

12:34.928 --> 12:37.539
You are staying
at the beach club. Okay?

12:37.669 --> 12:39.280
- Okay.
- All right. Great.

12:39.410 --> 12:41.195
- All right. Come on,
ladies. This way.
- Okay. Okay.

12:41.325 --> 12:42.587
- Bye, baby.
- Bye-bye.

12:42.718 --> 12:43.850
Come on. Come on.

13:06.960 --> 13:07.874
Hm.

13:11.791 --> 13:12.966
And you must be Ben.

13:16.230 --> 13:18.841
I'm Ashley.
I manage the beach club.

13:18.972 --> 13:20.669
I guess you met
my mum and dad.

13:20.800 --> 13:23.411
I'm Claire.
Ashley, did you say?

13:23.541 --> 13:24.891
Yes.

13:25.805 --> 13:28.068
Say something.

13:28.198 --> 13:29.417
I'm Ben.

16:09.055 --> 16:10.839
- Hey, baby.
- Hey, baby.

16:10.970 --> 16:12.406
It's really hot.
I'm gonna go take a shower

16:12.536 --> 16:14.321
and get changed.
You gonna come?

16:14.451 --> 16:16.062
No, I'm gonna stay here
for a while.

16:16.192 --> 16:18.238
Okay. Mwah.

16:20.936 --> 16:22.894
How's the club doing?
Has it changed?

16:23.025 --> 16:26.898
No. Well, it's dingier.

16:27.029 --> 16:29.292
We're only open
twice a week now,
post-COVID.

16:29.423 --> 16:31.773
You know, George and Alex
were the big pull
back in the day.

16:31.903 --> 16:33.383
When Theo and I were waiters,

16:33.514 --> 16:35.211
we could barely
get across the room.
It was packed.

16:35.342 --> 16:36.560
Yeah.

16:36.691 --> 16:38.736
Well, the world's changed.
We've changed.

16:40.347 --> 16:41.913
Have we?

16:42.044 --> 16:43.176
Mm-hmm.

16:46.831 --> 16:49.138
I'm glad
you're happy, George.

16:49.269 --> 16:51.358
We are... happy.

16:52.359 --> 16:53.447
Well, I mean, she is.

16:54.970 --> 16:58.321
Look, I know she's
a bit of an Energizer bunny,
and I'm not.

16:58.452 --> 17:00.497
Well, I mean...

17:00.628 --> 17:02.021
I used to be relentless
back in the day.

17:03.152 --> 17:04.893
Hey, don't even say it.

17:05.024 --> 17:06.982
Oh, Georgie, please.

17:07.113 --> 17:11.160
I'm just laying here,
biting my tongue
like a good friend.

17:11.291 --> 17:13.771
Look, she's not as bad
as you think she is, okay?

17:13.902 --> 17:15.512
Oh, George. No one
was thinking that.

17:15.643 --> 17:17.993
- You said it. Not me.
-  Alex,

17:18.124 --> 17:20.343
retract the claws
for once. Okay?

17:20.474 --> 17:23.651
Ah, leave her, Theo.
It's gonna come out
at some point.

17:23.781 --> 17:26.654
You love her, George,
and that's all that matters.

17:26.784 --> 17:28.743
- Thank you.
-  I mean, come on, guys.

17:28.873 --> 17:30.962
It can't be easy for her.
Look at us.

17:31.093 --> 17:33.661
We've known each other
for over 15 years.

17:33.791 --> 17:36.055
- Fifteen?
- Fifteen.

17:38.927 --> 17:39.884
We're old.

17:42.626 --> 17:43.801
I need a drink!

17:43.932 --> 17:47.196
- Hm.

18:25.408 --> 18:28.803
This is Chrishi Beach,
and it's all yours now, Ben.

18:30.979 --> 18:34.156
Yeah. I think I...

18:34.287 --> 18:36.115
I'm gonna need a drink.

18:36.245 --> 18:37.681
Pick your poison.

18:39.205 --> 18:40.684
So where are we staying?

18:40.815 --> 18:42.730
Oh, the beach house.
It's just over there.

18:42.860 --> 18:44.949
- Theo!
- Bye!

18:45.080 --> 18:46.212
Bye.

18:47.909 --> 18:50.477
Oh-ho. Oof.

18:50.607 --> 18:53.393
Robyn makes
the best cocktails
on the island.

18:53.523 --> 18:56.309
Robyn, meet Ben.
He's the new owner.

18:56.439 --> 18:58.398
And these are his friends,
Megan and George.

18:58.528 --> 19:00.835
Welcome to The Love Shack
Bar, guys.

19:00.965 --> 19:03.054
- What can I get you?
-  Hi.

19:03.185 --> 19:06.928
I would love
a frozen margarita.

19:08.190 --> 19:11.933
George, this is not Cancun.
This is Nevis.

19:12.063 --> 19:13.500
I can do better than that.

19:13.630 --> 19:15.371
Well, fantastic.
Surprise us, please.

19:15.502 --> 19:17.286
Sounds good.
Coming right up.

19:17.417 --> 19:19.984
I'm gonna go dance, baby.
Come with me. Mwah.

19:20.115 --> 19:21.334
Come on. Come on.
Come on.

19:22.639 --> 19:24.032
I'm going dancing.

19:41.528 --> 19:43.573
Ugh. Disgusting.

19:43.704 --> 19:45.096
Hate it.
This won't do at all.

19:45.227 --> 19:46.663
Absolutely not.

19:46.794 --> 19:50.189
I'm going back to my cozy
kitchen-bathroom combo.

20:11.340 --> 20:14.082
- Ah!
- Who says you get
the best bedroom, bitch?

21:06.221 --> 21:07.614
Hi.

21:07.744 --> 21:09.572
Oh, my God, Claire!

21:09.703 --> 21:12.923
My bed feels like I'm sleeping
on Burt Reynolds'
chest hair-- lo.

21:13.054 --> 21:14.664
I'm Harry. I...
I work at the club.

21:14.795 --> 21:17.145
I didn't know
you guys arrived.
You need anything?

21:17.276 --> 21:19.539
No, thank you.
We're perfectly okay.

21:19.669 --> 21:22.933
Well, I shall have
to call you Prince Harry,

21:23.064 --> 21:25.588
for you are
a prince among men.

21:26.850 --> 21:29.331
Prince Harry? Okay.

21:29.462 --> 21:32.682
Well, I'll be at the club
if you do need anything.

21:32.813 --> 21:35.381
Well, thank you, my prince.

21:39.515 --> 21:41.648
Woman!
I know that look.

21:41.778 --> 21:44.172
I don't want to slap you,
but I will.

21:44.303 --> 21:46.217
You're thinking
of falling for that tall,

21:46.348 --> 21:49.395
impossibly good-looking man
with the perfect ass,
aren't you?

21:49.525 --> 21:53.877
No, definitely not.
Not interested at all.

21:54.008 --> 21:57.054
Sure, he's handsome, articulate,

21:57.185 --> 22:00.057
age-appropriate,
and apparently
gainfully employed.

22:00.188 --> 22:03.887
But I'm over men.
I'm just here
to focus on me.

22:04.018 --> 22:06.237
Okay, now how many times
have we heard that?

22:07.761 --> 22:08.805
Ah!

22:13.201 --> 22:15.856
I've never liked you!
Got my hair wet.

22:25.126 --> 22:27.563
Oh, and that guy
was shouting at you
because you were wearing fur.

22:27.694 --> 22:28.782
Oh, my God!

22:29.957 --> 22:31.567
Yes! And he was like,

22:31.698 --> 22:34.483
"What poor creature had to die
for you to wear this coat?!"

22:34.614 --> 22:36.267
- And you said?
- "My Aunt Vera."

22:36.398 --> 22:38.357
"May she rest in peace!"

22:38.487 --> 22:40.924
And, Theo, you were under
the table. What were you
doing under there?

22:41.055 --> 22:43.579
- Come on. What were you doing?
-  Oh, no! You're doing
all my questions!

22:43.710 --> 22:45.538
It was me.
Remember the heels?

22:45.668 --> 22:47.844
- Oh, the big ones!
They were gorgeous.
- They were gorgeous!

22:47.975 --> 22:50.847
But they were 7" heels.
I twisted my ankle,
my right ankle.

22:50.978 --> 22:53.981
The osteria was to the left.
I could only turn right, right?

22:54.111 --> 22:56.549
So, I'm under the table.
My leg is like this high.

22:56.679 --> 22:59.726
- Who's there with me
under the table?

22:59.856 --> 23:01.554
- Georgie!
- You lie.

23:01.684 --> 23:03.860
You lie.

23:03.991 --> 23:04.905
What was the owner's name?

23:05.035 --> 23:07.081
Luigi!

23:08.648 --> 23:10.084
God, it was too good.
It was too good.

23:10.214 --> 23:12.216
But seriously,
that poor guy.

23:12.347 --> 23:14.044
- But didn't he try
to throw us out?
- Baby...

23:14.175 --> 23:16.917
Yeah. Because--
would you blame him?
We were too noisy!

23:17.047 --> 23:19.963
Baby? I'm--
I'm gonna have
to step away, okay?

23:20.094 --> 23:21.312
- Okay.
-  Could you blame him?

23:21.443 --> 23:22.966
I mean,
come on.

23:23.097 --> 23:24.664
Yeah, but that's when we
pretended that we got married.

23:24.794 --> 23:26.492
I had too much fun.

23:26.622 --> 23:28.581
And then-- we were
at each other's throats
out at the club.

23:28.711 --> 23:29.843
That was amazing.

23:29.973 --> 23:31.453
How long do you all know
each other for?

23:31.584 --> 23:33.455
- Too long.
- Oh, gosh. Way too long.

23:33.586 --> 23:36.763
This one is the older brother
that I never had.

23:36.893 --> 23:39.287
Oh. I love you too.

23:42.246 --> 23:43.596
Hello.

23:44.553 --> 23:45.641
Charlie?

23:45.772 --> 23:47.991
I thought we were gonna
meet tomorrow.

23:48.122 --> 23:51.430
Yes, but I thought
I'd abandoned you
somewhat earlier.

23:51.560 --> 23:55.390
So, I saw the house lit up.
I said, "Why not?"

23:56.913 --> 24:01.352
Like the good old days.
The parties, the hijinks,
the goings-on.

24:03.529 --> 24:07.141
I just need your signature
and a witness.

24:07.271 --> 24:08.882
Perhaps
your charming friend.

24:14.844 --> 24:16.455
I'd love to.

24:19.327 --> 24:20.415
How to get a witness.

24:20.546 --> 24:22.112
- Hey, to the witness!

24:22.243 --> 24:24.637
- To the gorgeous witness.
-  Witness!

24:26.552 --> 24:29.163
I just love
your cooking. Ooh.

24:29.293 --> 24:31.252
-  Georgie, you...

24:31.382 --> 24:34.995
Mm. That is fabulous.
What is that?

24:35.125 --> 24:36.562
- It's my secret.
- Will you teach me?

24:36.692 --> 24:38.477
I wanna learn
how to cook like you.

24:38.607 --> 24:39.869
Of course I will, honey.

24:50.140 --> 24:51.838
So many nights...

24:53.013 --> 24:57.017
your father and I
would sit here,
drink rum,

24:57.147 --> 25:01.151
and have endless discussions
about life.

25:02.196 --> 25:03.632
The papers.

25:06.200 --> 25:08.898
Now, I have already marked
the signature pages

25:09.029 --> 25:11.640
for you and the witness
to sign.

25:23.870 --> 25:26.612
Very good. Now,
when we spoke on the phone,

25:26.742 --> 25:31.225
you expressed a desire
to perhaps sell the estate?

25:31.355 --> 25:33.009
Of course,
I can assist you with that,

25:33.140 --> 25:34.881
if that's
your intention.

25:35.011 --> 25:37.057
Uh, well,
about that...
I just, uh...

25:38.188 --> 25:40.539
I think I'm gonna need
a couple days to think
about that.

25:40.669 --> 25:44.368
This is huge.
Of course you need
time to think.

25:46.283 --> 25:49.025
Yes, take your time.

25:49.156 --> 25:51.419
Meanwhile, enjoy
our beautiful island.

25:51.550 --> 25:54.117
And if you decide to sell,

25:54.248 --> 25:57.904
there are already several
very interested buyers.

25:58.034 --> 25:59.514
Really?

26:00.994 --> 26:02.778
Could you give us
a moment, please?

26:02.909 --> 26:04.084
Of course.

26:06.260 --> 26:07.566
Thank you.

26:12.309 --> 26:16.575
- How do you feel?
- I feel pretty good,
I guess.

26:18.838 --> 26:21.188
More important question is,
Claire, how do you feel?

26:25.888 --> 26:27.542
I need a reset.

26:29.109 --> 26:31.981
All these years of trying
to find love...

26:34.070 --> 26:37.421
I'm done. I just need
to focus on me.

26:37.552 --> 26:39.859
I'm so happy you're here
with me. Thank you.

26:39.989 --> 26:41.295
Me too.

26:44.080 --> 26:47.301
So that's him?

26:48.258 --> 26:49.738
Yeah, that's him.

26:51.871 --> 26:54.308
I wish I knew
what he had in mind for me.

26:54.438 --> 26:56.571
I don't know what he's got
on his mind,

26:56.702 --> 27:00.575
but I know you've got
Ashley on yours.

27:02.969 --> 27:05.014
Ashley?

27:05.145 --> 27:06.537
Well, she is--

27:06.668 --> 27:07.930
Ravishing?

27:08.061 --> 27:10.933
Yes, exactly.
And she's too young for me.

27:11.064 --> 27:13.762
No, she's my age.
I already asked.

27:13.893 --> 27:15.546
And that would be 34?

27:15.677 --> 27:18.549
Yes. I have been
for the past five years,

27:18.680 --> 27:20.073
and I intend to stay there.

27:21.596 --> 27:24.773
Oh, I've missed you
so much.

27:24.904 --> 27:26.253
I missed you too.

27:27.428 --> 27:29.038
- Shall we?
- Yeah.

27:38.221 --> 27:39.570
Oof.

27:40.789 --> 27:43.705
- Be happy.
- I am.

27:47.448 --> 27:49.276
Yeah,
but you were so drunk,
you fell off your chair.

27:49.406 --> 27:51.670
Ha! I'm Russian.
I feel [speaks Russian].

27:53.323 --> 27:54.455
Ben.

27:56.065 --> 27:57.371
This one's for you,
my friend.

28:01.070 --> 28:03.029
Okay, baby.

