<i>♪ Of life ♪</i>

29:36.775 --> 29:39.734
Bravo! Bravo!
Whoo-hoo.

29:39.865 --> 29:42.084
Bravo. Bravo.

29:42.215 --> 29:44.652
Daddy...

29:44.783 --> 29:47.350
- Can you relax, please?
- I am relaxed.

29:47.481 --> 29:49.962
Right. I can see that.

29:50.092 --> 29:51.702
They're good guys.

29:52.791 --> 29:55.924
I think he's getting ready
to sell Golden Rock.

29:56.055 --> 30:00.146
- I can feel it.
- Don't be so pessimistic.

30:00.276 --> 30:03.236
Just let them enjoy
their time here.

30:03.366 --> 30:06.369
Daddy? Please?

30:18.773 --> 30:20.557
I'd like to make a toast.

30:23.256 --> 30:25.562
To Arnie Sandoval.

31:04.079 --> 31:07.256
Arnie would have...
he would have just loved this!

31:09.563 --> 31:11.304
What was he really like?

31:11.434 --> 31:13.872
The man was a legend.

31:14.916 --> 31:17.963
It would take days
to do him justice.

31:18.093 --> 31:20.356
Just a remarkable fellow.

31:20.487 --> 31:23.359
When I first came here
from the States,

31:23.490 --> 31:25.274
Arnie helped me
get set up here.

31:25.405 --> 31:28.625
He was like... the mayor,

31:28.756 --> 31:30.149
the don of the island,

31:30.279 --> 31:32.325
the pope of the Caribbean.

31:35.241 --> 31:36.895
I owe him everything.

31:40.681 --> 31:42.465
It's peaceful here.

31:45.077 --> 31:49.168
Nevis is a place where peace
and harmony is everything.

31:56.784 --> 31:57.741
Charlie...

31:59.308 --> 32:01.876
Do a lot of people
come to the island
just to get married?

32:02.007 --> 32:06.359
Dozens of marriages,
maybe dozens of dozens.

32:06.489 --> 32:10.841
And that includes
quite a few pitched in
by yours truly.

32:10.972 --> 32:15.934
I've married and divorced
four Mrs. Brooks
on this very island.

32:16.064 --> 32:18.327
If you're gonna have
miserable divorces,

32:18.458 --> 32:21.113
you may as well have
magical weddings.

32:23.680 --> 32:26.466
That's exactly
what I was thinking.

32:28.685 --> 32:29.948
Come on.

32:33.603 --> 32:34.953
You're impossible.

32:37.172 --> 32:39.827
- What are you
smiling about?

32:41.655 --> 32:44.788
I'm thinking
about how lucky I am...

32:44.919 --> 32:47.574
right now in this moment,
in this place.

32:47.704 --> 32:48.879
Right here.

32:49.706 --> 32:52.753
I finally found out
who my father was,

32:52.883 --> 32:55.364
where I came from.

32:55.495 --> 32:57.627
Sitting here
in this beautiful place...

32:59.890 --> 33:02.023
with my dearest friends
in the world.

33:03.590 --> 33:05.331
Yeah, I'm lucky.

33:06.941 --> 33:08.856
And I just wish
it would never end.

33:08.987 --> 33:10.989
What if it doesn't have to?

33:11.119 --> 33:13.252
What if we just... stay?

33:14.514 --> 33:15.863
A little tipsy, Claire?

33:15.994 --> 33:18.387
I'm drunk, but not on rum.

33:18.518 --> 33:20.041
Must be the beer.

33:20.172 --> 33:22.130
No. It's this place.
It's this moment.

33:22.261 --> 33:23.871
I'm drunk
on the possibilities.

33:24.002 --> 33:25.003
What possibilities?

33:25.133 --> 33:26.743
Of us being here together.

33:27.657 --> 33:29.311
What if we open
a wedding business?

33:29.442 --> 33:31.748
You are drunk.

33:31.879 --> 33:32.923
No, think about it.

33:33.054 --> 33:35.491
- "Paradise Weddings."
- Claire.

33:35.622 --> 33:37.667
I'm happy, finally.

33:37.798 --> 33:41.193
It took me six years
of therapy after my divorce.

33:41.323 --> 33:43.195
I--

33:43.325 --> 33:46.154
I don't believe in marriage,
and I don't think
you believe in it either.

33:46.285 --> 33:48.548
I have to believe in them.

33:49.505 --> 33:50.637
Please.

33:54.945 --> 33:56.382
You got the floor.

33:57.426 --> 33:59.428
Guys! Guys, okay,
I've got an idea.

33:59.559 --> 34:02.083
And I know
it's gonna sound crazy,
but just please hear me out.

34:02.214 --> 34:04.955
What would you say
about staying here?

34:05.086 --> 34:06.740
- She's drunk.
- Just for a while...

34:06.870 --> 34:09.090
for a few months
or like a year,

34:09.221 --> 34:11.092
just so that we can be
together again,

34:11.223 --> 34:14.313
and just live,
and love, and laugh,

34:14.443 --> 34:17.316
- and have fun, and breathe.
-  I love it!

34:17.446 --> 34:19.144
- Doing what?
-  Yeah.

34:19.274 --> 34:21.059
Romantic weddings
at the beach club.

34:21.189 --> 34:23.496
- Oh.
- Just think about it.

34:23.626 --> 34:27.978
The sand, and the sun, and--
and the ocean, and romance.

34:28.109 --> 34:29.893
It's perfect.

34:30.024 --> 34:32.940
And come on, none of us are
particularly happy right now.

34:33.071 --> 34:34.333
- Oh, well--

34:34.463 --> 34:35.812
You might want
to speak for yourself,

34:35.943 --> 34:38.293
because George and I are
really happy together.

34:39.468 --> 34:40.469
Urgh.

34:40.600 --> 34:41.949
Okay, well,
I'm not happy.

34:42.080 --> 34:44.473
And I think I speak
for most of us

34:44.604 --> 34:46.084
when I say we hate our jobs.

34:46.214 --> 34:49.696
And I hate being single
in my stupid flat in London.

34:49.826 --> 34:52.568
And, Theo and Alex, I know
that you guys feel
the same way.

34:52.699 --> 34:56.311
- Yeah.
- So, what if we
just start fresh here?

34:56.442 --> 34:58.748
I'll put it to the guys.
What do you think?

34:58.879 --> 35:00.098
What do we think?

35:00.228 --> 35:01.751
Claire, come on.

35:01.882 --> 35:04.232
What on Earth
do any of us know
about weddings?

35:04.363 --> 35:05.799
I mean, we're not exactly,

35:05.929 --> 35:08.149
you know, shining example
of marital bliss here, okay?

35:08.280 --> 35:09.542
- Hmm.

35:09.672 --> 35:11.805
Oh, come on, babe.
Look at the rest of us.

35:11.935 --> 35:15.025
I mean, single. Single.
Celibate nymphomaniac...

35:15.156 --> 35:16.853
- Ah!
- ...which is a hell
of a condition,

35:16.984 --> 35:18.246
but we're still miserable.

35:18.377 --> 35:20.074
Yeah.
But look, come on.

35:20.205 --> 35:21.945
Even if that was the case,
I mean, we can't
just up sticks,

35:22.076 --> 35:24.905
- and just leave
everything behind.
- Yeah.

35:25.035 --> 35:26.472
But why not?

35:26.602 --> 35:29.736
Come on!
This place is special.

35:29.866 --> 35:32.739
Megan, you heard
how George sang tonight.

35:32.869 --> 35:34.828
That's the George
we know and love.

35:36.003 --> 35:37.744
And, Alex, come on.

35:37.874 --> 35:39.093
Do you really want to be
teaching Chopin

35:39.224 --> 35:41.443
to spoiled rich kids forever?
You hate it.

35:41.574 --> 35:43.706
It's true. I do hate it.

35:43.837 --> 35:46.405
And, Theo,
you haven't even touched
your camera for two years,

35:46.535 --> 35:48.581
and you have nothing
to go back for.

35:48.711 --> 35:51.105
Wow! Tell it like it is.

35:51.236 --> 35:54.891
I mean, how do you
propose to do this plan?

35:55.022 --> 35:57.024
Well, um, I could do
the marketing,

35:57.155 --> 35:59.722
and-- and Ben can be
the host with the most,

35:59.853 --> 36:01.202
like he was back in the day.

36:01.333 --> 36:04.553
And every wedding,
I guess, needs music, so...

36:04.684 --> 36:06.990
- Yes!
- And I suppose I could
do some singing.

36:07.121 --> 36:08.253
<i>♪ Look for... ♪</i>

36:08.383 --> 36:10.777
And I can prepare
the food with Lois!

36:10.907 --> 36:12.474
I could be a bridesmaid!

36:12.605 --> 36:14.824
- Or... ?
- Or I could take
the photographs.

36:14.955 --> 36:17.523
If it's of any help,
I'm an ordained minister.

36:17.653 --> 36:20.047
I always knew it would
come in handy one day.

36:20.178 --> 36:22.267
It's perfect!
We could totally do this!

36:22.397 --> 36:24.704
We can totally do this.
Please say yes, please.

36:24.834 --> 36:26.314
Please, please, please.

36:33.103 --> 36:34.453
To one year off!

36:42.635 --> 36:45.812
- What's going on?
- Looks like we're staying.

39:20.706 --> 39:22.185
Hi, Claire.

39:22.316 --> 39:24.971
You're blocking
my view, Barry.

39:35.634 --> 39:37.940
By the way, it's Harry.

39:38.071 --> 39:41.683
Right. So,
is this your job?

39:42.858 --> 39:44.860
Kind of.

39:44.991 --> 39:47.428
I've been working at the club
ever since I drifted
into this paradise.

39:47.559 --> 39:50.039
Sheldon, Lois and Ashley
are like family to me.

39:51.824 --> 39:54.043
That's very nice
to hear, Larry.

39:56.176 --> 39:57.307
It's Harry.

39:57.438 --> 39:58.570
Sorry?

40:00.180 --> 40:01.399
Never mind.

40:02.704 --> 40:04.314
So, Ashley tells me
that you and your friends

40:04.445 --> 40:06.316
are going to be here
for a whole year.

40:06.447 --> 40:10.146
Maybe. I didn't pack
my crystal ball.

40:11.409 --> 40:13.628
Well, you could always borrow
my Magic 8-Ball in a pinch.

40:15.804 --> 40:17.197
That's a good joke, Jerry.

40:19.591 --> 40:21.810
It's still Harry.

40:21.941 --> 40:23.551
That it is.

40:23.682 --> 40:27.076
Well, okay then.
I'm gonna get back
to the club.

40:28.730 --> 40:31.167
I'm just gonna lie here
for a bit longer.

40:31.298 --> 40:32.473
Bye, Claire.

40:58.586 --> 40:59.674
- Hey.
- Hey.

40:59.805 --> 41:01.720
I was wondering,
have you seen my wife?

41:01.850 --> 41:03.765
Uh, yeah. She went
to the market with Lois.

41:03.896 --> 41:04.984
Oh, good.

41:07.639 --> 41:09.205
This is the best.

41:09.336 --> 41:10.642
I found my father's diaries.

41:10.772 --> 41:12.513
- Yeah?
- Ooh.

41:12.644 --> 41:15.385
Here, have a read.
Just read anything.

41:19.041 --> 41:21.261
"Last night,
Rudy Nureyev--"

41:21.391 --> 41:23.089
- Nureyev?
- Nureyev.

41:24.873 --> 41:26.919
"...came over. Such a hoot.

41:27.049 --> 41:29.748
We drank too much vodka
and I beat him at whist.

41:29.878 --> 41:32.838
His ankle was swollen,
and I made him sit with it
above his head,

41:32.968 --> 41:35.536
because it always
does the trick."

41:35.667 --> 41:38.234
- Really, Nureyev?
- Nureyev.

41:38.365 --> 41:41.368
Turns out that my father
truly was a legendary person.

41:41.499 --> 41:43.718
Everything everybody's saying
about him is true.

41:43.849 --> 41:46.155
I mean, he knew everybody.
I'm talking everybody.

41:46.286 --> 41:48.070
He knew Khrushchev,
Che Guevara.

41:48.201 --> 41:51.160
He talks about rolling cigars
with Fidel Castro.

41:51.291 --> 41:52.771
- Castro?
- Yeah. Castro.

41:52.901 --> 41:55.730
- Really?
- It's incredible.
But my favorite...

41:55.861 --> 41:59.342
He knew Ernest Hemingway personally.

41:59.473 --> 42:01.301
He talks about swapping
mojito recipes

42:01.431 --> 42:03.303
with Ernest friggin' Hemingway.

42:05.479 --> 42:07.829
And let me tell you,
there's tons of this stuff.
I mean, it's everything--

42:07.960 --> 42:11.267
it's important,
it's funny, it's fascinating.

42:11.398 --> 42:13.139
I mean, fascinating.

42:15.402 --> 42:17.796
- Hemingway? Hmm.
- Hemingway.

42:33.202 --> 42:36.162
Hold my <i>matryoshkas</i> .
Gentlemen, hello.

42:36.292 --> 42:38.947
- Hey, how are you doing?
- Oh, I'm doing
just fine, thank you.

42:39.078 --> 42:40.079
Have a nice day.

42:40.862 --> 42:42.864
Well, you're going young,
aren't you?

42:42.995 --> 42:45.563
First of all,
they are in their early 20s,

42:45.693 --> 42:50.089
and I am in my early
to [coughs] mid-40s. Okay?

42:50.219 --> 42:52.395
- Cougar.
- Yeah. And your point?

42:54.180 --> 42:56.443
Oh, excuse me.
He is very cute.

42:59.446 --> 43:01.796
- Go easy on my guests.
- Oh, please stop.

43:01.927 --> 43:03.232
You know me.
I'm just looking.

43:03.363 --> 43:06.801
Hey! And I'm liking.

43:08.281 --> 43:09.412
Claire?

43:11.197 --> 43:12.502
Hello, sweetheart.

43:13.852 --> 43:15.375
About last night...

43:15.505 --> 43:17.072
- Yes?
- Um...

43:17.203 --> 43:20.554
Maybe we should hammer out
some of those ideas you have.

43:22.774 --> 43:25.254
I was worried you might have
changed your mind
after the alcohol evaporated.

43:25.385 --> 43:28.649
No, I've never been more sure
of anything in my life, Claire.

43:29.519 --> 43:30.782
Me too.

43:33.001 --> 43:35.613
- Well, first things first.
- What?

43:37.049 --> 43:39.747
Well, now we have to find
someone who wants
to get married.

43:39.878 --> 43:42.881
Oh. Funny
you should say that.

43:45.623 --> 43:47.668
Caroline!
I know, I'm sorry.

43:47.799 --> 43:50.105
No, I...
I wasn't ignoring you.

43:50.236 --> 43:51.498
I should have
called you back.

43:51.629 --> 43:53.631
But I'm calling you now.

43:54.719 --> 43:58.418
Yes, I know. Awful.
I'm so sorry.

43:58.548 --> 44:01.203
Yes. But listen, Caroline.

44:01.334 --> 44:04.337
What would you say
to a romantic wedding

44:04.467 --> 44:07.732
on the most beautiful beach
in the world?

44:07.862 --> 44:10.865
That's the thing.
It <i>could</i> happen.

44:10.996 --> 44:12.388
I could <i>make it</i> happen.

44:19.265 --> 44:21.006
We've got
our first customer, guys.

44:22.964 --> 44:25.010
We are open for business.

44:25.140 --> 44:27.229
Yeah!

